# Scenario: SIM NOT DETECTED — SIMCom SIM7600G-H, customer reports
# "device shipped from factory and won't connect."
# Key signals:
#   +CPIN: NOT INSERTED      (modem cannot read the UICC)
#   +CCID -> +CME ERROR: 10  (SIM not inserted)
#   +CIMI -> +CME ERROR: 10
#   +CSQ: 99,99              (no measurement — radio not initialized)
# Diagnosis: this is a hardware-side problem before any network interaction.
# Common causes ranked by frequency in field returns:
#   1. SIM tray inserted with wrong orientation (chip up vs chip down).
#   2. SIM contacts dirty or corroded — wipe with isopropyl, reseat.
#   3. Ribbon cable / SIM holder solder joint damaged in shipping.
#   4. Modem firmware in download mode (rare, would also fail to boot AT cleanly).
# Customer guidance:
#   - Power down completely.
#   - Reseat the SIM, verify orientation against the silkscreen.
#   - Try a known-good SIM in the same slot — if it also fails, hardware fault.
#   - Try the suspect SIM in a known-good device — if it works, slot fault.
# Triage tip: ALWAYS distinguish "SIM not inserted" from "SIM PIN locked" — different
# fix paths.

